The Vice President delivered remarks at the 2019 National Veterans Day Observance at Arlington National Cemetery. He expressed gratitude to all veterans for their service and emphasized that every veteran is a hero. The Vice President highlighted President Trump's commitment to supporting veterans, including passing reforms for the Department of Veterans Affairs and increasing funding for mental health services. He also mentioned the President's efforts to expand education benefits for veterans and improve the economy for returning veterans. The Vice President pledged to continue supporting the military and honoring the sacrifices made by veterans. He encouraged all Americans to find a veteran and express their gratitude on Veterans Day.